Amazon Review Sentiment Analysis

Project Overview
This project analyzes Amazon customer reviews and classifies them as positive or negative using Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning techniques.

Objective
To build a sentiment classification model that helps businesses understand customer feedback and improve product decisions.

Technologies Used
Python
Pandas
Scikit-learn
TF-IDF Vectorization
Matplotlib

Process
Text cleaning and preprocessing
Feature extraction using TF-IDF
Model training and evaluation
Performance comparison

Models Used
Naive Bayes
Logistic Regression

Results
The model successfully classified customer reviews with high accuracy and demonstrated the effectiveness of machine learning for sentiment analysis tasks.

Business Impact
Identify negative customer feedback
Improve product quality
Support data-driven decision-making
